00:26:09,783 --> 00:26:10,597
Hello.

492
00:26:10,722 --> 00:26:14,233
<i>What feeds
on human blood 5 times a day?</i>

493
00:26:19,886 --> 00:26:21,036
I don't know.

494
00:26:22,063 --> 00:26:23,522
Why don't you tell me?

495
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:24,916
<i>Lice.</i>

496
00:26:25,309 --> 00:26:27,376
<i>What insects fly alone in the dark?</i>

497
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:30,296
<i>Do you give up?</i>

498
00:26:31,706 --> 00:26:32,790
<i>Locusts.</i>

499
00:26:33,369 --> 00:26:34,759
Please, where's Oliver?

500
00:26:35,795 --> 00:26:37,524
<i>I know, but you don't.</i>

501
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:43,158
What makes you think
I can break this hold?

502
00:26:43,561 --> 00:26:45,311
You're the lawyer. You tell me.

503
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:47,411
You got into this mess
by threatening violence.

504
00:26:47,536 --> 00:26:49,649
You could have always
checked in voluntarily.

505
00:26:49,817 --> 00:26:52,526
No, I needed to be on the locked ward
so I could talk to Beth.

506
00:26:53,016 --> 00:26:54,518
When she mentioned the pied piper,

507
00:26:54,643 --> 00:26:56,864
she was talking about a real person,
so I need to get out.

508
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:58,909
You could call Foster and Reynolds.

509
00:26:59,188 --> 00:27:00,743
They could always handle it.

510
00:27:00,911 --> 00:27:03,162
I already used up my phone privilege
when I called you.

511
00:27:04,456 --> 00:27:06,025
So are you gonna help me or what?

512
00:27:09,744 --> 00:27:12,923
Though I find it fascinating you feel
like I'm the only one you can call,

513
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:15,091
and yet we can't even have
a real adult conversation.

514
00:27:15,382 --> 00:27:16,926
Right. What do you wanna know?

515
00:27:17,649 --> 00:27:20,096
Why don't you try telling me
how you really feel?

516
00:27:22,787 --> 00:27:24,137
All right. I'm...

517
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:26,894
I'm upset,

518
00:27:28,211 --> 00:27:29,272
and I'm scared,

519
00:27:30,524 --> 00:27:33,343
and I'm really,
really, really rattled.

520
00:27:35,587 --> 00:27:36,594
I give up.

521
00:27:36,719 --> 00:27:39,398
You actually want me to try to convince
the doctor that you're not insane?

522
00:27:39,523 --> 00:27:40,848
It's worth a shot, right?

523
00:27:48,141 --> 00:27:50,084
Locust and darkness.

524
00:27:50,478 --> 00:27:52,586
None of this is random.
He has a plan.

525
00:27:52,980 --> 00:27:55,899
Also, he got angry when Faye didn't
know the rules to bloody murder.

526
00:27:56,024 --> 00:27:58,467
He's controlling
and very detail-oriented.

527
00:27:58,765 --> 00:28:00,052
It's the 10 plagues.

528
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:03,431
Frogs, lice, locusts,
blood, darkness.

529
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:05,641
And the death of firstborn sons.

530
00:28:05,809 --> 00:28:07,932
Rex was the eldest. So is Oliver.

531
00:28:08,057 --> 00:28:10,062
Everybody,
give us 5 minutes, please?

532
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:11,480
Come on. Let's go.

533
00:28:13,317 --> 00:28:14,317
You know,

534
00:28:15,044 --> 00:28:17,956
speaking of lunatics,
when I said you sounded insane,

535
00:28:18,081 --> 00:28:20,335
I didn't mean for you to go check
into a psych ward.

536
00:28:20,460 --> 00:28:23,117
- I know.
- You went to see Wilkie's exgirlfriend.

537
00:28:23,691 --> 00:28:26,422
I couldn't resist it.
It turns out...

538
00:28:27,812 --> 00:28:29,248
Wilkie's not workin' on his own.

539
00:28:29,416 --> 00:28:32,626
All right, the pied piper
is a nickname for a real person.

540
00:28:33,217 --> 00:28:35,004
They went to music camp together.

541
00:28:35,172 --> 00:28:36,392
In the fairy tale,

542
00:28:36,517 --> 00:28:40,217
the pied piper plays
some sort of flute or clarinet.

543
00:28:40,342 --> 00:28:42,303
Maybe that's what he played
at music camp.

544
00:28:42,992 --> 00:28:45,473
You know, whoever it is,
he's got all the answers.

545
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:47,850
You do know...

546
00:28:48,863 --> 00:28:50,895
that I'm not gonna
just walk away from this.

547
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:54,037
So tell the bureau to fire me...

548
00:28:54,574 --> 00:28:56,313
and to find another Lightman group.

549
00:28:56,438 --> 00:28:58,861
- Good luck on that, by the way.
- Just be right this time.

550
00:28:59,245 --> 00:29:00,561
I'll do my level best.

551
00:29:08,247 --> 00:29:09,288
You okay?

552
00:29:10,476 --> 00:29:11,957
Yeah, I'm fantastic.

553
00:29:12,456 --> 00:29:13,848
I'm here if you need me.

554
00:29:14,261 --> 00:29:15,544
You know that, right?

555
00:29:15,930 --> 00:29:16,930
Right.

556
00:29:18,561 --> 00:29:19,733
I know that, love.

557
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:28,848
Hello.

558
00:29:28,973 --> 00:29:31,480
So mom has some pictures laid out
from the Wilkie trial,

559
00:29:31,605 --> 00:29:33,519
a few months after you guys met.

560
00:29:33,644 --> 00:29:35,606
She's looking a little
rounder than usual.

561
00:29:35,989 --> 00:29:36,791
And?

562
00:29:36,916 --> 00:29:38,994
And we've never really
discussed it before,

563
00:29:39,119 --> 00:29:40,528
but I'm pretty good at math.

564
00:29:41,788 --> 00:29:42,863
Your point being?

565
00:29:43,312 --> 00:29:46,075
I was born 7 1/2 months
after you guys married.

566
00:29:47,019 --> 00:29:48,290
Would you believe...

567
00:29:49,146 --> 00:29:50,663
that you were premature?

568
00:29:51,057 --> 00:29:52,832
At 8 pounds, 8 ounces?

569
00:29:53,676 --> 00:29:55,558
No, your mum was pregnant
when I married her.

570
00:29:55,683 --> 00:29:58,337
But you couldn't have just
come out and told me that?

571
00:29:58,462 --> 00:30:00,414
No, we didn't want
to celebrate our mistakes,

572
00:30:00,539 --> 00:30:01,966
have you go on and copy 'em.

573
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:04,019
- So I was a mistake?
- Course not.

574
00:30:05,162 --> 00:30:08,025
So how'd it happen? Were you drunk?

575
00:30:08,150 --> 00:30:11,725
Was it just a one-night stand?
Did you even go on a date first?

576
00:30:12,864 --> 00:30:13,864
Yes,

577
00:30:14,292 --> 00:30:15,499
no, and yes.

578
00:30:16,616 --> 00:30:17,848
What's the matter, em?

579
00:30:18,708 --> 00:30:22,148
Did you only marry mom
because you got her pregnant?

580
00:30:22,273 --> 00:30:24,900
No. No, of course not.
I'm not that much of a gentleman.

581
00:30:25,533 --> 00:30:27,870
No, be serious.
I wanna know if I'm the reason

582
00:30:27,995 --> 00:30:30,578
you guys spent
14 miserable years together.

583
00:30:32,635 --> 00:30:34,485
Look, I married your mum...

584
00:30:34,950 --> 00:30:36,208
because I loved her.

585
00:30:36,638 --> 00:30:39,292
Then you comin' along
just helped me pull the trigger.

586
00:30:39,927 --> 00:30:42,010
Plus they were by no means

587
00:30:42,135 --> 00:30:44,432
14 miserable years.

588
00:30:46,048 --> 00:30:47,048
So...

589
00:30:47,850 --> 00:30:50,764
I didn't, like, ruin your life
or something like that?

590
00:30:51,837 --> 00:30:54,114
No, you were
the best news I ever got.

591
00:30:55,468 --> 00:30:56,604
Still are.

592
00:30:57,810 --> 00:31:00,257
- So you were drunk.
- Yeah.

593
00:31:00,789 --> 00:31:02,503
- It wasn't a one-night stand.
- No.

594
00:31:02,628 --> 00:31:04,313
- And you were dating.
- Yeah.

595
00:31:05,423 --> 00:31:08,115
I married your mum
'cause I loved her.

596
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,250
If I had to do it all over again...

597
00:31:12,807 --> 00:31:14,343
No, I take that back.

598
00:31:17,479 --> 00:31:19,375
Studies show
that the strongest deterrent

599
00:31:19,500 --> 00:31:21,803
to a lawsuit is familiarity,
a personal relationship.

600
00:31:21,928 --> 00:31:24,035
So I figure I establish
a rapport with Kevin.

601
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:27,328
It'll be much harder for him to sue
knowing it'll affect my livelihood.

602
00:31:27,453 --> 00:31:29,220
Well, I'm goin' with you,

603
00:31:29,388 --> 00:31:32,519
if this works, I'm not letting you
take all the credit for saving Lightman.

604
00:31:32,644 --> 00:31:33,928
And if it doesn't work?

605
00:31:34,053 --> 00:31:38,057
Then it's all your fault, I'm gonna call
the Rader firm and set up an interview.

606
00:31:39,524 --> 00:31:43,150
So, anyway, we just wanted to come by
and see how you were doing.

607
00:31:43,608 --> 00:31:44,818
Last time we saw you,

608
00:31:45,424 --> 00:31:48,724
you were pretty upset,
understandably, so... and, uh...

609
00:31:48,907 --> 00:31:51,575
We...
Well, we brought you some pastries.

610
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:57,414
I know firsthand what stress can do.
It can...

611
00:31:57,582 --> 00:32:00,341
You call what I've been
going through just stress?

612
00:32:00,466 --> 00:32:02,586
Dr. Lightman tried
to stop the execution.

613
00:32:02,994 --> 00:32:04,588
He's devoted himself to the case.

614
00:32:04,756 --> 00:32:06,924
He's close to find if someone
elsehad been involved.

615
00:32:07,049 --> 00:32:09,593
That doesn't change the fact that Jason
is dead because

616
00:32:09,761 --> 00:32:11,136
your boss made a mistake.

617
00:32:11,469 --> 00:32:15,473
Let's cut to the chase. Why are you
here? Convince me not to sue Lightman.

618
00:32:17,565 --> 00:32:20,165
I know this might seem pretty weird,
but,

619
00:32:22,018 --> 00:32:24,068
if there's anything you need...

620
00:32:24,780 --> 00:32:26,530
Or if you just wanna talk

621
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:28,870
or something, that's my number.

622
00:32:34,736 --> 00:32:37,236
It was really nice
getting to know you.

623
00:32:40,458 --> 00:32:41,584
Thank you.

624
00:32:42,074 --> 00:32:44,712
No one can even look me
in the eye these days,

625
00:32:45,284 --> 00:32:46,630
so I appreciate it.

626
00:32:50,112 --> 00:32:53,512
Maybe I'll hold off on suing Lightman
till I learn what he finds.

627
00:32:57,649 --> 00:32:59,699
<i>I did not hurt that little boy.</i>

628
00:33:00,109 --> 00:33:02,409
<i>You want me to confess, but I won't.</i>

629
00:33:06,513 --> 00:33:08,563
<i>I did not hurt that little boy.</i>

630
00:33:09,013 --> 00:33:11,313
<i>You want me to confess, but I won't.</i>

631
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:21,996
<i>Do you know who the
first liar in the world was?</i>

632
00:33:23,301 --> 00:33:24,301
The devil.

633
00:33:25,413 --> 00:33:29,417
- In the bible, he's the father of lies.
- <i>Is Zoe a lawyer or a liar?</i>

634
00:33:30,673 --> 00:33:32,843
Nah, if we're playin'
20 questions here,

635
00:33:33,406 --> 00:33:37,410
I think it's my turn.
What's your deal with eldest sons?

636
00:33:38,509 --> 00:33:41,560
<i>Do you know where your daughter is?</i>

637
00:33:42,695 --> 00:33:44,615
<i>Can she come out and play?</i>

638
00:33:53,899 --> 00:33:55,049
<i>Dial by name.</i>

639
00:33:56,076 --> 00:33:57,076
Emily.

640
00:33:57,302 --> 00:33:58,302
<i>Emily.</i>

641
00:34:00,932 --> 00:34:02,764
- Emily.
- <i>Hey, Cal, it's me.</i>

642
00:34:02,889 --> 00:34:04,790
<i>Emily left her phone.
She went to see you.</i>

643
00:34:04,915 --> 00:34:06,669
She left my place about an hour ago.

644
00:34:07,411 --> 00:34:08,761
We got a problem.

645
00:34:09,265 --> 00:34:12,362
Hannah said she never picked up Emily.
Tell me exactly what happened.

646
00:34:12,487 --> 00:34:15,177
I got a call on my private line,
asking me if I knew where Emily was.

647
00:34:17,036 --> 00:34:18,186
Was that him?

648
00:34:19,077 --> 00:34:20,347
What did he say?

649
00:34:20,517 --> 00:34:24,228
Cal Lightman, calling for
Agent Reynolds. Well find him.

650
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:27,231
- Tell him it's an emergency.
- What did he say?

651
00:34:27,399 --> 00:34:30,734
The FBI will start a search.
We should just cool. Emily's friends...

652
00:34:34,871 --> 00:34:38,272
I told you Haley was picking me up.
We just went to get something to eat.

653
00:34:40,138 --> 00:34:41,245
You said Hannah.

654
00:34:41,551 --> 00:34:42,901
No, I said Haley.

655
00:34:44,967 --> 00:34:48,971
First there are the phone calls. Then,
he takes your child. That's the pattern.

656
00:34:50,033 --> 00:34:53,132
Let's go through all this stuff again.
What's in that box?

657
00:34:55,217 --> 00:34:58,192
Photos that Wilkie's mother gave me
during the trial to prove

658
00:34:58,317 --> 00:35:00,514
that Jason was a good boy.

659
00:35:02,137 --> 00:35:03,851
Rex was kept alive for 3 days.

660
00:35:04,019 --> 00:35:06,437
- News clippings aren't relevant.
- All is relevant.

661
00:35:06,605 --> 00:35:08,522
A killer is after our daughter,
the only way

662
00:35:08,690 --> 00:35:11,859
to keep her safe is to catch him.
You don't decide what's relevant or not.

663
00:35:12,027 --> 00:35:15,549
That's precisely what the killer wants,
to panic us into stopping our search.

664
00:35:15,674 --> 00:35:18,699
The best way that we can
end this is to find him.

665
00:35:19,323 --> 00:35:21,160
I just wanna keep her safe.

666
00:35:24,064 --> 00:35:26,660
Well, the FBI's parked
right outside.

667
00:35:28,405 --> 00:35:30,005
I can't take any more.

668
00:35:32,878 --> 00:35:34,089
You can do this.

669
00:35:50,206 --> 00:35:54,210
Those photographs from Wilkie's mum,
are they from when he was a kid?

670
00:35:55,730 --> 00:35:58,447
Well, the Pied Piper and Jason
knew each other when they were kids,

671
00:35:58,615 --> 00:36:00,282
so there might be something there.

672
00:36:06,636 --> 00:36:08,536
Kevin's the youngest, right?

673
00:36:10,046 --> 00:36:11,668
Look at the body language.

674
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:15,840
He's clearly in control. He's dominant.
The other 2, older 2, they adore him.

675
00:36:16,583 --> 00:36:17,883
And who's the older one?

676
00:36:19,433 --> 00:36:20,433
William.

677
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:25,644
Wilkie's mother said that her oldest son
died of pneumonia when he was a kid.

678
00:36:33,876 --> 00:36:35,576
Oh, my God. It's Kevin.

679
00:36:38,796 --> 00:36:40,096
With a clarinet.

680
00:36:42,839 --> 00:36:46,843
Kevin is the pied piper, right?
He made the phone calls.

681
00:36:47,122 --> 00:36:50,046
He kidnapped Rex,
but he had Jason kill him.

682
00:36:50,406 --> 00:36:51,745
- They were partners.
- Why?

683
00:36:52,120 --> 00:36:55,382
It was revenge for the death
of their eldest brother, William.

684
00:36:55,507 --> 00:36:59,511
William came down with pneumonia after
their father lost his job at the diner.

685
00:37:00,228 --> 00:37:02,886
The diner was torn down
by the Sheridan company,

686
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:05,592
- their first development deal.
- The family was worried about money,

687
00:37:05,717 --> 00:37:08,238
they didn't take him to the hospital.
He died after 3 days.

688
00:37:08,363 --> 00:37:11,228
So they blamed the Sheridan
family enough to kill Rex?

689
00:37:11,396 --> 00:37:15,009
And after Jason was executed,
Kevin had to take revenge again.

690
00:37:15,134 --> 00:37:16,803
We found Kevin's car.

691
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:19,581
He's long gone, and there's no sign
of Oliver at his house.

692
00:37:19,706 --> 00:37:21,165
We must have tipped him off.

693
00:37:21,290 --> 00:37:23,657
We told him Lightman was close
to finding the culprit.

694
00:37:24,582 --> 00:37:28,584
If his M.O. is to kill the victim on the
3d day, Oliver could be dead already.

695
00:37:33,878 --> 00:37:35,678
All right, hit the lights.

696
00:37:40,257 --> 00:37:43,857
Well, the GPS on Kevin's car
shows us he was here 3 days ago.

697
00:37:44,026 --> 00:37:47,402
He was chief engineer on this project
before it was shut down a month ago.

698
00:37:47,527 --> 00:37:51,018
All right, everybody. Keep your eye
and your ears open. Let's fan out.

699
00:38:09,844 --> 00:38:11,044
You hear that?

700
00:38:14,829 --> 00:38:17,962
There's someone in there. Give me
something to open this thing up with.

701
00:38:18,087 --> 00:38:19,087
Come on!

702
00:38:24,854 --> 00:38:25,954
Ah, damn it!

703
00:38:33,329 --> 00:38:36,229
I hate rats.
Pritchard, you stay with Lightman.

704
00:38:36,418 --> 00:38:39,268
You three, come with me.
Let's check upstairs.

705
00:39:00,201 --> 00:39:01,630
This doesn't belong here.

706
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:11,420
Yeah, hold this.

707
00:39:32,189 --> 00:39:33,889
Oliver, can you hear me?

708
00:40:01,983 --> 00:40:04,109
Hold it right there. Don't move.

709
00:40:04,788 --> 00:40:05,888
Cal, you OK?

710
00:40:06,373 --> 00:40:08,776
- Yeah, he's in the wall.
- Let me see your hands.

711
00:40:08,901 --> 00:40:10,952
- Check on Oliver.
- We got an agent down.

712
00:40:11,077 --> 00:40:12,177
Right on it.

713
00:40:18,982 --> 00:40:22,201
Mr. Sheridan, I owe you an apology.

714
00:40:22,326 --> 00:40:24,029
Sorry about being such an ass.

715
00:40:24,154 --> 00:40:26,298
Forget it.
And thank you for everything.

716
00:40:26,679 --> 00:40:27,679
Pleasure.

717
00:40:27,904 --> 00:40:30,167
You're bleedin'.
You don't wanna go to the hospital?

718
00:40:30,292 --> 00:40:32,742
Nah, these guys
are gonna patch me up.

719
00:40:35,163 --> 00:40:36,566
How about, uh, Wilkie?

720
00:40:36,691 --> 00:40:38,846
We found equipment
he used to make the calls.

721
00:40:38,971 --> 00:40:42,505
- He's not talkin' yet, but he's stable.
- Stable? He's an animal.

722
00:40:42,666 --> 00:40:45,566
If I had my way,
he wouldn't be talking at all.

723
00:40:46,339 --> 00:40:47,389
Good stuff.

724
00:40:51,844 --> 00:40:55,140
Beato Michaeli archangelo,
beato Ioanni...

725
00:40:55,265 --> 00:40:56,328
Turn that off.

726
00:40:58,260 --> 00:40:59,960
- Are you OK?
- Peachy.

727
00:41:02,292 --> 00:41:05,921
I got hold of Jason Wilkie's footage
just before his execution.

728
00:41:06,163 --> 00:41:08,006
His final prayer was in Latin.

729
00:41:08,231 --> 00:41:10,029
It was a confession of sins.

730
00:41:10,154 --> 00:41:12,344
Maybe it was his way
of taking the blame

731
00:41:12,569 --> 00:41:14,669
for... for killing Rex Sheridan.

732
00:41:15,270 --> 00:41:19,274
Well, I'd like to think this is over,
but, I've been wrong before, so...

733
00:41:20,742 --> 00:41:22,815
- We never doubted you, Cal.
- Really?

734
00:41:22,940 --> 00:41:25,581
- Not for a second.
- Really?

735
00:41:31,854 --> 00:41:34,074
- I had your back.
- Oh, yeah?

736
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,035
Well, I had an exit plan, too.

737
00:41:37,260 --> 00:41:38,610
Yeah. Jack Rader.

738
00:41:39,580 --> 00:41:41,172
I'd have done the same thing.

739
00:41:41,297 --> 00:41:42,397
Pays better.

740
00:41:50,345 --> 00:41:51,550
Ooh, sorry.

741
00:41:51,903 --> 00:41:53,228
You're enjoying this.

742
00:41:53,353 --> 00:41:56,221
No, I'm doing nothing of the sort.
I'm like Florence Nightingale.

743
00:41:56,741 --> 00:42:00,566
You could make your life a lot easier
if you admit that you need people.

744
00:42:00,691 --> 00:42:02,477
You don't have to be
such a lone wolf.

745
00:42:03,344 --> 00:42:06,439
Aw, do me a favor. With you two
and Foster and the rest of the group,

746
00:42:06,607 --> 00:42:09,151
- it's a 3-ring bloody circus.
- You know what I mean.

747
00:42:09,393 --> 00:42:12,215
Let the record reflect
that Zoe Landau is correct.

748
00:42:12,340 --> 00:42:14,290
- You happy now?
- Ecstatic.

749
00:42:15,233 --> 00:42:16,533
OK, don't move.

750
00:42:18,729 --> 00:42:19,744
Don't move.

751
00:42:21,854 --> 00:42:22,914
You're all set.

752
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:26,018
- Really?
- Yeah. Let's go get something to eat.

753
00:42:26,143 --> 00:42:29,921
Hey, I'm sorry you guys thought
I was missing earlier.

754
00:42:30,147 --> 00:42:32,174
I thought of a perfect solution

755
00:42:32,349 --> 00:42:34,092
to make sure
that never happens again.

756
00:42:34,217 --> 00:42:35,927
Oh, yeah? Let's hear it.

757
00:42:36,776 --> 00:42:39,231
Buy me a car.
I mean, think about it.

758
00:42:39,432 --> 00:42:43,436
You'll never have to get confused
about who's picking me up.

759
00:42:44,578 --> 00:42:47,625
- That's clever, that is.
- She gets her craftiness from you.

760
00:42:47,750 --> 00:42:49,149
Yeah, not bloody likely.

761
00:42:49,827 --> 00:42:51,972
So is... is that a yes?

762
00:42:56,682 --> 00:42:58,082
Dream on, darlin'.

